      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "In the first year of Cyrus the king of Babylon.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Recent discoveries of contract tablets have shown that at Babylon Cyrus bore the title of \"king of Babylon\" from the date of his conquest of the city. The same title was passed on to his successors, Cambyses, Darius, etc. Hence we find Artaxerxes Longimanus called \"king of Babylon\" by Nehemiah (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 13:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Ezra 5:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
